  "texts": [
    "[22] mentioned that recurrent neural networks (RNNs) have a variant called LSTM models used to find patterns in data sequences.",
    "To create predictions, RNNs can use the context and location of a sequence.",
    "Regular RNNs, on the other hand, only have short-term memory and have trouble with longer sequences.",
    "LSTM models address this problem by including both long-term and short-term memory.",
    "According to Dolphin [5], LSTM networks were created to address the recurrent neural networks' long-term reliance issue."
  ],
